                    <div class='right' style='float:right;width:40%;margin-top:30px'>
                        <ol> <li> Remove all of the arrows coming into $\textbf{v}$ </li>
                            <li> Replace $\textbf{v}$ with the constant variable $x$. </li>
                            <li> All other conditional probabilities remain the same. </li>
                        </ol>

                    </div>
				</section>

				<section>
                    <h2>Causation</h2>
                    <small> We can write down what the interventional distribution is explicitly in terms of the model parameters (here $\textbf{W}$ is a subset of the variables) </small>
                    \[
                    \text{Pr}(\textbf{W} = w | \text{do}(\textbf{X} = x)) =
                    \]
                    \[
                    \sum_{\textbf{V}_i \not \in \textbf{W}}\prod_{\textbf{V}_i \in V \setminus X} \text{Pr}(\textbf{V}_i = v_i | \text{pa}(\textbf{V}_i) = \text{pa}(v_i), \textbf{X} = x)
                    \]
				</section>

                <section>
                    <h2>Unobserved Variables</h2>
                    <small> Not all variables are known in general. </small>

                    <small> Unobserved variables can make the result of an intervention ambiguous. </small>
                    <svg width="700px" height="800px" viewBox="-40 0 800 100">
                          <defs>
                            <marker id="arrowheada" markerWidth="10" markerHeight="7"
                            refX="0" refY="3.5" orient="auto">
                              <polygon points="0 0, 10 3.5, 0 7" fill="#FFFFFF"/>
                            </marker>
                          </defs>
