                        Outcome
                        </text>
                      </svg>

                </section>

                <section>
                    <h3 style="color:#EEAAAA">Can we conclude correlation from causation?</h3>
                    <p style="font-size:30px"> A graph with marked unobserved variables is said to be <b>identifiable</b> if for any consistent distribution on the observed variables, there is a unique interventional distribution. </p>
                    <p style="font-size:30px"> A complete classification of identifiable graphs was given in Tian and Pearl in 2002, including an algorithm for determining if a given network is identifiable. </p>
                </section>

                <section>
